                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Build a Plex Media Server With These October Prime Day Deals]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/plex-prime-day-october-2025/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Andrew Heinzman]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/28-1.jpg" length="288" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Plex]]></category><category><![CDATA[Amazon Prime Day 2025]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Free yourself from monthly streaming fees with this discounted server hardware.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Tired of paying for streaming services like Netflix and HBO Max? Maybe it's time to set up a Plex media server. The price of entry is somewhat steep, but there are plenty of great home server deals during Prime Big Deals Day (October 7th and 8th), so now's a good time to spend a couple hundred bucks and decouple yourself from all those monthly streaming fees.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 19:32:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/plex-prime-day-october-2025/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[It's Hurricane Season, Here's How I Protect My Computer from Power Outages and Surges]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/its-hurricane-season-heres-how-i-protect-my-computer-from-power-outages-and-surges/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Patrick Campanale]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/portable_power_stations_in_front_of_a_hurricane_warning_sign_with_palm_trees_blowing_in_strong_winds.png" length="2420" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Portable Power Station]]></category><category><![CDATA[Anker 2100J 12-Port Surge Protector]]></category><category><![CDATA[battery]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Don't wait until it's too late to plan for power outages.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Has your power ever gone out for days (or weeks) at a time? Mine has, and I learned a lot during that time. Here’s how I keep all of my technology safe when the power flashes or goes out completely due to crazy weather.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 19:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/its-hurricane-season-heres-how-i-protect-my-computer-from-power-outages-and-surges/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[My Everyday Keyboard From Logitech Is 20% Off Today]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/my-everyday-keyboard-from-logitech-is-20-off-today/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Corbin Davenport]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/logitech-pop-icon-keys.jpg" length="874" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Logitech]]></category><category><![CDATA[Keyboards]]></category><description><![CDATA[
