                                            There are tons of unique gizmos out there for those with eyes to see.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Do you long for the days when you had dedicated devices, like brick phones, PDAs, CD players, and handheld game consoles? Do the smartphones that have taken the role of all those devices bore you? I've got good news: the world of fun little gadgets is alive and well.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 18:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/smartphones-havent-replaced-everythingjust-check-out-these-gadgets/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Google Messages Is Getting Another Powerful New Feature]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/google-messages-is-getting-another-powerful-new-feature/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Cory Gunther]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/google-messages-logo-1.jpg" length="1452" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apps & Web Apps]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Messages]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Take control of video messages. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Do you want more control over the types of texts, images, and videos you get on Google Messages? If so, we have some good news. This week, we learned that Google is rolling out an optional new feature to prevent NSFW and other unwanted videos from appearing on your phone.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 17:18:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/google-messages-is-getting-another-powerful-new-feature/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The iPad Mini With an A17 Pro Chip Is Just $379 Today]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/the-ipad-mini-with-an-a17-pro-chip-is-just-379-today/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/apple-ipad-mini-7.jpg" length="1430" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPad mini (2024)]]></category><category><![CDATA[Deals]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            There's a huge discount on the newest iPad Mini.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>You can get the newest Apple iPad Mini for an incredible <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DK3YF38G/?tag=hotoge-20&ascsubtag=UUhtgUeUpU2017166&asc_refurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2Fthe-ipad-mini-with-an-a17-pro-chip-is-just-379-today%2F&asc_campaign=Affiliate" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">$379.00 on Amazon</a> for a limited time. This is a 24% discount from its original price of $499.00, making this a great price for the latest version of Apple's tablet.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 16:57:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/the-ipad-mini-with-an-a17-pro-chip-is-just-379-today/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Python 3.14 Has Arrived With T-String Support]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/python-314-has-arrived-with-t-string-support/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/python-logo-over-blurred-python-code-background-with-the-word-python-written-in-yellow-underneath.png" length="2949" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Programming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Python]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Template string literals are finally coming to Python, and other improvements.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Python 3.14 is officially here, and brings a mix of changes to the core language, the interpreter's guts, and the standard library. These are major updates like template string literals, deferred evaluation of annotations, and even official support for subinterpreters in the standard library.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 16:44:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/python-314-has-arrived-with-t-string-support/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[8 Useful Things You Can Plug Into Your Car's OBD2 Port]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/useful-things-you-can-plug-into-your-cars-obd2-port/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Cory Gunther]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/illustration-showing-a-car-s-interior-with-a-highlighted-obd-port-surrounded-by-devices-like-the-bluedriver-dongle-a-car-hud-and-the-scangauge-display.png" length="2115" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Electric Vehicles]]></category><category><![CDATA[DIY]]></category><category><![CDATA[iPhone]]></category><category><![CDATA[SUVs]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Plug in all the things. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Have you ever looked under your car's steering wheel at all the wires, fuses, and plugs? If so, you might find an odd plug called an OBD-II port. That's the same port any technician uses during a smog test, and mechanics access it to scan for check engine light errors, but that's not all it can do. You can plug several useful or weird things into that 16-pin port. </p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 16:30:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/useful-things-you-can-plug-into-your-cars-obd2-port/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[From Snatch to Adolescence: 12 of Stephen Graham’s Best Roles Ever]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/stephen-graham-best-film-television-roles/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Keeley Brooks]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/collage-of-stephen-graham-in-a-thousand-blows-adolescence-boardwalk-empire-and-boiling-point.png" length="2693" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[TV Shows]]></category><category><![CDATA[ Movies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Adolescence]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            See how the esteemed actor evolved into an award-winning powerhouse.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Esteemed British actor Stephen Graham is finally seeing the stardom he has long deserved. The chameleon of talent recently won his first Primetime Emmy for his role in the hit <a href="https://www.netflix.com/" target="_blank">Netflix</a> psycho-drama series <em>Adolescence</em>. Weeks prior to its release, Graham snatched viewers’ attention with his powerhouse portrayal of 19th-century boxer Sugar Goodson in <a href="https://disneyplus.bn5x.net/c/156932/564546/9358?subId1=UUhtgUeUpU2017108&subId2=ehtg&u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hulu.com%2Fwelcome&ourl=http%3A%2F%2Fhulu.com%2F" class="norewrite noskim" rel="sponsored nofollow" target="_blank">Hulu</a>’s <em>A Thousand Blows</em>.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 16:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/stephen-graham-best-film-television-roles/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Notepad++ Just Got an Update With a New Clipboard Trick]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/notebook-got-an-update-heres-whats-new/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/notepad-logo-on-a-blue-background.jpg" length="41" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Notepad++]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Making Notepad++ even better.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Notepad++ just dropped version 8.8.6, and now you can finally paste multiple lines of text directly into the Find and Replace fields. You no longer have to rely on workarounds or plugins for multi-line text manipulation, among other fixes.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 15:33:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/notebook-got-an-update-heres-whats-new/</guid></item></channel>
